name: H3CClient
body:
### Introduction
H3CClient for OS X is an H3C-specialized 802.1x protocol authentication client including a front-end monitor, based on previous work [h3cclient b1](http://sourceforge.net/projects/h3cclient/) by asklux. This client has been verified working for students from Shandong University.

### Downloads
No stable version released yet.

### Contact & Support
If any bugs encountered or support needed, please submit a bug report via [Github Issues](https://github.com/5Ki3s0x1C9/OS-X-H3CClient/issues). 
Reverse engineering of the H3C protocol credits to the efforts of previous work.
